1
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:57,200
I should have known when we broke up three years ago.

2
00:00:57,880 --> 00:00:59,439
Some people are like chronic allergies.

3
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:01,600
You think you're cured,

4
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:03,240
but as soon as you meet again,

5
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:05,799
all the symptoms come back.

6
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:07,000
Next, let's welcome...

7
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:07,959
For example, now,

8
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,239
when I look at him through the camera,

9
00:01:10,599 --> 00:01:12,239
my heart beats like a drum in my ear.

10
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:14,879
Leading figure in youth aviation technology,

11
00:01:14,879 --> 00:01:16,120
core engineer,

12
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:17,359
Yun Fei.

13
00:01:17,359 --> 00:01:19,040
What's worse,

14
00:01:19,519 --> 00:01:21,079
we're about to become

15
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,159
brother and sister.

16
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:29,319
Sorry.

17
00:01:29,599 --> 00:01:30,200
Sorry.

18
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:30,959
Are you okay?

19
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,280
I'm fine.

20
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:03,280
You're so meddlesome.

21
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,280
If you don't want to wear it, take it off.

22
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:08,719
No one's forcing you.

23
00:02:09,319 --> 00:02:10,879
If you don't want to talk nicely, don't follow me.

24
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:11,879
No one's forcing you either.

25
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:21,879
We broke up three years ago.

26
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,520
You still have the habit of

27
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:26,560
not losing out in words.

28
00:02:28,719 --> 00:02:29,719
You've changed a lot.

29
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,000
You're so considerate.

30
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:32,599
Thank you for your shirt.

31
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,360
But back then,

32
00:02:35,439 --> 00:02:36,560
when I was unconscious from a fever,

33
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,879
you didn't even answer the phone.

34
00:02:38,479 --> 00:02:39,639
I've never seen you so thoughtful.

35
00:02:48,199 --> 00:02:48,840
What are you doing?

36
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:54,960
Applying medicine.

37
00:03:01,319 --> 00:03:02,560
No, I can do it myself.

38
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,840
You don't think I still like you, do you?

39
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,759
When we broke up,

40
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,439
you said the kiss at the bar

41
00:03:15,319 --> 00:03:16,319
was because you were drunk.

42
00:03:17,639 --> 00:03:18,120
Was it?

43
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:22,759
Yes.

44
00:03:47,039 --> 00:03:48,879
I was just going along with you

45
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:50,039
at that time.

46
00:03:51,319 --> 00:03:52,039
Here, give you back.

47
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,120
That's fine.

48
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,520
We're even now.

49
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,719
That way,

50
00:04:00,639 --> 00:04:02,280
I didn't take advantage of you for nothing, right?

51
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:17,800
What do you mean?

52
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:21,120
Don't get me wrong. The shirt money.

53
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:23,720
Xiaochuan,

54
00:04:24,279 --> 00:04:25,079
are you in there?

55
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,199
Xiaochuan,

56
00:04:26,759 --> 00:04:27,360
are you okay?

57
00:04:27,879 --> 00:04:28,759
I'm fine.

58
00:04:32,279 --> 00:04:32,920
Who is that?

59
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:34,560
My boyfriend.

60
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,600
Do you want to meet him?

61
00:04:52,199 --> 00:04:52,720
Let's go.

62
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,839
Sorry about that.

63
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,439
I shouldn't have said you're my boyfriend.

64
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,319
I thought you weren't joking.

65
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,360
Anyway, thank you for inviting me to the exhibition.

66
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,879
If your video needs editing next time,

67
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:16,639
just let me know.

68
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,160
But there's one thing I need to make clear to you.

69
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,439
Don't fall for me.

70
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:23,920
You're great,

71
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,279
but we're not right for each other.

72
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:26,560
Doctor Lan,

73
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,319
do you have to be so blunt?

74
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,560
Yes, I do.

75
00:05:31,879 --> 00:05:33,040
Anyway, just to be clear,

76
00:05:33,279 --> 00:05:35,279
you'll promote my family's clinic next time.

77
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,399
I'll send you the contract once it's drafted.

78
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:37,959
It'll be three percent more than a regular deal.

79
00:05:39,519 --> 00:05:40,199
Looking forward to a smooth cooperation.

80
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,480
Me too.

81
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,160
Hello, Auntie.

82
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,360
[Xiao Fei,]

83
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,759
[I need to remind you of something.]

84
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,360
[Your mom has been]

85
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,759
[acting all secretive lately,]

86
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,439
[making calls in private,]

87
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,279
[and always heading to the TCM clinic.]

88
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:07,959
TCM clinic?

89
00:06:11,519 --> 00:06:12,040
Morning, Chuan.

90
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:12,600
Morning.

91
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:13,639
Morning.

92
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:14,879
Morning, Chuan.

93
00:06:20,759 --> 00:06:21,600
What's the issue?

94
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:26,240
Doctor Lan, my heart

95
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,560
keeps fluttering.

96
00:06:28,759 --> 00:06:30,000
Now that I see you,

97
00:06:30,879 --> 00:06:31,720
I feel at ease.

98
00:06:32,199 --> 00:06:34,439
Chinese medicine emphasizes inspection, auscultation, inquiry, and palpation.

99
00:06:35,199 --> 00:06:37,360
Your inspection is impressive.

100
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,800
Roses given,

101
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:41,560
hands

102
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,920
leave fragrance behind.

103
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,079
You're healthy, just a bit of internal heat.

104
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,639
Heartburn.

105
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:53,879
It's quite fiery.

106
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,240
Wrist bone acupoint connects to the heart meridian,

107
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:01,000
which clears heat.

108
00:07:01,399 --> 00:07:02,519
No, it's sore.

109
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,439
That's normal, just hold on.

110
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:13,480
Flowers again?

111
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,319
Trash.

112
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,199
Old man,

113
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,680
you've waxed your head.

114
00:07:21,279 --> 00:07:23,000
Even mosquitoes have to do splits to land.

115
00:07:23,959 --> 00:07:24,639
What do you know?

116
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:29,040
I'm doing this for the clinic's image.

117
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,399
Everyone,

118
00:07:31,879 --> 00:07:32,920
put your work aside.

119
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,240
It's lunch break.

120
00:07:34,519 --> 00:07:35,360
Order something tasty.

121
00:07:35,439 --> 00:07:37,639
I'll treat you today.

122
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,240
What?

123
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,639
Why do we have a lunch break so often recently?

124
00:07:40,879 --> 00:07:42,560
Last month, we just talked about increasing the number of patients.

125
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:44,560
This is called work-life balance.

126
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:45,240
Here.

127
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,040
Take it.

128
00:07:48,399 --> 00:07:50,680
Go order your favorite sweet and sour pork.

129
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:51,399
Remember,

130
00:07:51,439 --> 00:07:53,240
add more sweet and sour sauce.

131
00:07:56,199 --> 00:07:57,800
Go.

132
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:27,879
Xiao Fei,

133
00:08:28,079 --> 00:08:29,920
I'm afraid that if your mom got sick,

134
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,480
she wouldn't tell you.

135
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,000
Pay attention to her when you come back.

136
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:43,639
Are you stalking me?

137
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:44,840
What do you mean?

138
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,600
Who's stalking you?

139
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,200
This is my clinic.

140
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:52,320
You're sneaking around like a burglar.

141
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,919
It can't be a coincidence, can it?

142
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,399
Your clinic?

143
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,840
Blood pressure is 120 over 80.

144
00:09:09,279 --> 00:09:10,279
Very healthy.

145
00:09:10,879 --> 00:09:12,399
Very healthy.

146
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,399
That's good.

147
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:17,080
[Why is my heart]

148
00:09:19,879 --> 00:09:22,000
[beating so fast?]

149
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,159
[Annoying.]

150
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,200
I didn't eat this morning.

151
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,320
Maybe you have low blood sugar.

152
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,320
I'll give you some sugar.

153
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,519
Who is this old rascal?

154
00:09:38,399 --> 00:09:39,480
My dad.
